In [17]:
# encode the categorical variables

# EDUCATION:
# Creating new variables based on 'EDUCATION':
housing_df.loc[:, 'EDU_PRIMARY_SCHOOL'] = (housing_df['EDUCATION'] <= 2).astype(np.int64)
housing_df.loc[:, 'EDU_HIGH_SCHOOL'] = housing_df['EDUCATION'].between(3, 6).astype(np.int64)
housing_df.loc[:, 'EDU_COLLEGE'] = (housing_df['EDUCATION'] > 6).astype(np.int64)

# MARITAL_STATUS:
# Creating new variables based on 'MARITAL_STATUS':
housing_df.loc[: , 'MARRIED'] = (housing_df['MARITAL_STATUS'] <= 2).astype(np.int64)
housing_df.loc[: , 'DIVORCED'] = (housing_df['MARITAL_STATUS'].between(3, 4)).astype(np.int64)
housing_df.loc[: , 'SINGLE'] = (housing_df['MARITAL_STATUS'] >= 5).astype(np.int64)

In [62]:
from sklearn import svm

def f_importances(coef, names):
    imp = coef
    imp,names = zip(*sorted(zip(imp,names)))
    plt.barh(range(len(names)), imp, align='center')
    plt.yticks(range(len(names)), names)
    plt.title("Feature Importance for Strong Predictors")
    plt.show()

features_names = housing_df[['ROOMS', 'AGE','HOUSEHOLD_INCOME','EDU_PRIMARY_SCHOOL', 'EDU_HIGH_SCHOOL', 'EDU_COLLEGE',
       'MARRIED', 'DIVORCED', 'SINGLE']]
f_importances(np.abs(svm_linear_best.coef_[0]), features_names)

# Visualization code (new model used)

y_min, y_max = df_plot['HOUSEHOLD_INCOME'].min() - 1, df_plot['HOUSEHOLD_INCOME'].max() + 1
xx, yy = np.meshgrid(np.arange(x_min, x_max, 1), 
                      np.arange(y_min, y_max, 1))

Z = svm_plot.predict(np.c_[xx.ravel(), yy.ravel()]) # Using the retrained model
Z = Z.reshape(xx.shape)

plt.scatter(df_plot['ROOMS'], df_plot['HOUSEHOLD_INCOME'], c=y, s=20, cmap='viridis')

# FEATURE IMPORATANCE:

# Get the indices of support vectors
support_vector_indices = svm_radial_best.support_

# Get the support vectors
support_vectors = X_train.iloc[support_vector_indices]

# Get the dual coefficients (alphas) of the support vectors
dual_coefficients = svm_radial_best.dual_coef_.ravel()

# Calculate the importance scores for each feature
feature_importances = (support_vectors * dual_coefficients[:, np.newaxis]).sum(axis=0)

# Create a DataFrame to display the feature importances
feature_importance_df = pd.DataFrame({'Feature': X_train.columns, 'Importance': feature_importances})

# Sort the DataFrame by importance score
feature_importance_df = feature_importance_df.sort_values(by='Importance', ascending=False)

# Display the feature importances
print(feature_importance_df)
